 {"id":"bd-sbt21","title":"sprintf executor returns 'unsupported printf arg value' for float %e","description":"execute_sprintf_case in frankenlibc_conformance cannot dispatch certain printf conversions (observed: sprintf_e_basic with 12345.0). Surfaced while wiring bd-12hh printf_conformance harness matrix. Those specific fixture cases are skipped in the harness-matrix tests until the executor gains broader conversion support.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-21T20:00:37.882801746Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T05:46:00.070271168Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T05:46:00.068275622Z","close_reason":"parse_printf_args now always routes JSON float literals to PrintfArg::Double; added PrintfArg::NullPtr + 3/4/5-arg dispatch arms for star-width, multiple-conversion, mixed-type, and consecutive-int fixtures. Remaining executor gaps tracked in bd-0u5fm/bd-luc3d/bd-vgrav/bd-qij6l via KNOWN_IMPL_GAPS. Committed a4789ab.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-sch1","title":"CONFORMANCE: libc sched.h diff matrix","description":"Differential harness shipped (see commit). 7 functions: sched_yield (return value), sched_get_priority_min/max (5 policies SCHED_OTHER/FIFO/RR/BATCH/IDLE + invalid policy), sched_getscheduler (self + INT_MAX edge), sched_getparam (self priority match), sched_getaffinity (128B mask byte-exact match). Setters intentionally excluded (CAP_SYS_NICE required, would mutate process state). 8 tests, 0 divergences against glibc.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-frankenlibc","created_at":"2026-04-24T13:15:00Z","created_by":"cod-frankenlibc","updated_at":"2026-04-24T13:15:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T13:15:00Z","close_reason":"Harness shipped; 0 divergences.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance","differential","sched"]}
 {"id":"bd-sdov","title":"Conformance: direct execute process_ops fixture cases","description":"Add direct execute_fixture_case coverage for process_ops.json and extend the shared executor for safe process fixtures such as getpid/getppid/fork/waitpid, correcting fixture expectations for POSIX wait semantics if needed.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"SilverHarbor","created_at":"2026-04-18T11:40:07.819647246Z","created_by":"SilverHarbor","updated_at":"2026-04-18T11:52:26.960881901Z","closed_at":"2026-04-18T11:52:26.958979169Z","close_reason":"Added direct execute_fixture_case coverage for process_ops fixtures, implemented safe process executor coverage for getpid/getppid/fork/waitpid, and corrected WNOHANG/no-child expectation to ECHILD; verified with rch focused test/check/clippy.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance","process","testing"]}
