+{"id":"bd-se52q","title":"Optimize core strchrnul miss scan with benchmark proof","description":"Spec-first parity/performance slice for the safe Rust string core: benchmarked/prof-checked hot string primitives, rejected a measured memcmp chunk-skip attempt after Criterion showed regression, then optimized strchrnul to preserve target-or-terminator semantics in one pass instead of strchr+strlen double scanning on misses. Verification target: core string tests, ABI strchrnul tests, fmt/check/clippy, and Criterion before/after evidence.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T20:12:04.655532282Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T20:22:57.622285549Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T20:22:57.620320734Z","close_reason":"completed: optimized core strchrnul miss path to single-scan semantics; preserved memcmp ordering via regression test; verified with Criterion before/after, fmt, workspace check, UBS, and focused string tests","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["parity","performance","string"]}
 {"id":"bd-sem1","title":"CONFORMANCE: libc semaphore.h diff matrix","description":"Differential harness shipped (see commit). 7 functions: sem_init+sem_destroy (4 initial values 0/1/5/100), sem_post (3 posts from 0 → value 3), sem_wait (3 waits from 5 → value 2), sem_trywait at zero (fails on both), sem_trywait at 1 (succeeds on both), sem_timedwait with past-expiry abs timeout, sem_getvalue. Named sem_open deferred (shm cleanup complexity). 7 tests, 0 divergences against glibc.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-frankenlibc","created_at":"2026-04-24T14:30:00Z","created_by":"cod-frankenlibc","updated_at":"2026-04-24T14:30:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T14:30:00Z","close_reason":"Harness shipped; 0 divergences.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance","differential","semaphore"]}
 {"id":"bd-sh-1","title":"PORT: shadow sub-bead 1 — core::pwd::shadow parser","description":"Extend crates/frankenlibc-core/src/pwd/shadow.rs with: ShadowEntry { name: Vec<u8>, passwd: Vec<u8>, lstchg, min, max, warn, inact, expire: i64, flag: u64 }; parse_shadow_numeric(s: &[u8]) -> i64 (-1 sentinel for empty/non-numeric, matching glibc); parse_shadow_line(line: &[u8]) -> Option<ShadowEntry> (8+ colon fields, blank/comment skip); lookup_shadow_by_name(content, name) (case-sensitive, matches /etc/shadow lookup semantics). Comprehensive tests covering: typical line, all-sentinel-empty fields, missing optional flag, comment/blank skip, fewer than 8 fields rejected, parse-then-format round-trip with the existing format_shadow_line.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-24T10:14:42.768220Z","created_by":"cod-frankenlibc","updated_at":"2026-04-24T10:19:48.660063Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T10:19:48.660063Z","close_reason":"Extended crates/frankenlibc-core/src/pwd/shadow.rs (which already had format_shadow_line from bd-pgs) with: pub struct ShadowEntry (name, passwd: Vec<u8>; lstchg/min/max/warn/inact/expire: i64; flag: u64); parse_shadow_numeric(s: &[u8]) -> i64 returning -1 sentinel for empty/non-numeric; parse_shadow_line(line) -> Option<ShadowEntry> with EOL strip + comment/blank skip + 8-field minimum; lookup_shadow_by_name (case-sensitive per POSIX login-name semantics). Importantly: the missing/empty 9th flag field decodes to u64::MAX (matching glibc ~0UL convention) so parse->format identity is preserved for both -1 and u64::MAX sentinels. 27 tests cover all field shapes including round-trip property tests against format_shadow_line.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-sh-2","title":"PORT: shadow sub-bead 2 — rewire abi shims","description":"Drop parse_shadow_field + fill_shadow_entry from pwd_abi.rs. Drop the inline parsers from unistd_abi.rs::fgetspent / fgetspent_r. Each caller now: (1) calls core::pwd::shadow::parse_shadow_line; (2) packs name+passwd into the caller buffer with NULs; (3) writes the seven numeric fields directly from ShadowEntry. Verify any shadow-related abi tests still pass.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-24T10:14:42.768220Z","created_by":"cod-frankenlibc","updated_at":"2026-04-24T10:19:48.660063Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T10:19:48.660063Z","close_reason":"Removed parse_shadow_field from pwd_abi.rs (~7 lines) and the ~36-line inline parse+pack body in unistd_abi.rs::fgetspent and again in fgetspent_r. Refactored fill_shadow_entry to delegate to core::pwd::shadow::parse_shadow_line + pack name/passwd into TLS buffer. Added fill_shadow_entry_caller helper for the reentrant variants — getspnam_r and getspent_r each shrink from ~40 lines to ~10 (single core call + result wiring). The C-ABI SpwdEntry layout-stable struct stays in abi. Side-effect correctness fix: empty 9th flag field now decodes to ~0UL per glibc, so parse(format(x)) == x for the sentinel cases. 42/42 pwd_abi tests, 178/178 unistd_abi tests, 173/173 abi lib tests all pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
